crossguid
------------------------------------------
CrossGuid is a minimal, cross platform, C++ GUID library. It uses the best
native GUID/UUID generator on the given platform and has a generic class for
parsing, stringifying, and comparing IDs.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.3.5-1
  libgcc1-11.3.0-1
  libstdc++6-11.3.0-1
  libuuid1-2.33.1-2
  libxg-devel-0.2.2-1bl1
  libxg0-0.2.2-1bl1
  pkg-config-1.9.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.39-1
  cmake-3.23.2-1
  cygport-0.35.2-1
  gcc-core-11.3.0-1
  gcc-g++-11.3.0-1
  libuuid-devel-2.33.1-2
  ninja-1.11.0-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/graeme-hill/crossguid

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/graeme-hill/crossguid/archive/refs/tags/v0.2.2.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack crossguid-0.2.2-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./crossguid-0.2.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/crossguid-0.2.2-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/crossguid-0.2.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libxg0-0.2.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libxg-devel-0.2.2-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(crossguid)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/crossguid.README
  /usr/share/doc/crossguid/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/crossguid/README.md

(libxg0)
  /usr/bin/cygxg-0.dll

(libxg-devel)
  /usr/include/crossguid/Guid.hpp
  /usr/lib/libxg.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/crossguid.pc

